# BUGFIX/ROBUSTNESS under lead-m1dc (P1, product authority 2026-06-29): "... and
# if at all possible be able to update the tokens after the fact as well."
# Follow-on to lead-al1r (the approve-claude oauth fix, shop-templates v0.47.0 /
# 08136da oauth-tokens path). Target: the rendered ops script
# "bin/agent-vault-approve-claude".
#
# This is the UPDATE-TOKENS-AFTER-THE-FACT pin (single behavior): a later re-run
# to UPDATE an already-populated CLAUDE_OAUTH credential (re-POST fresh token
# material to the oauth-tokens endpoint) is a supported, non-error path. It is the
# operator-facing counterpart to the idempotency pin 220 — 220 pins that a re-run
# does not BREAK on prior state; 221 pins that a re-run is the SUPPORTED way to
# refresh the tokens later. Siblings: 219 (@scenario_hash:3b7e07095a354e0a) and 220
# (@scenario_hash:9aa82d211517155d). TIGHTENS robustness; does NOT retire scenario
# 202 (@scenario_hash:1c054dfdc468860a, non-blank-writeback) — the updated
# credential is still non-empty.
#
# @bc: and the reproducing @scenario_hash on dispatch are the Architect's; the
# block-only @scenario_hash below is the PO's authoring hash.
@scenario_hash:45dc18d4b0d1730e
Scenario: the rendered "bin/agent-vault-approve-claude" supports updating the CLAUDE_OAUTH tokens after the fact — a later re-run re-POSTs fresh token material to the oauth-tokens endpoint as a supported, non-error path
  Given a "lead" shop bootstrapped by "shop-templates" with the rendered ops script "bin/agent-vault-approve-claude" and an already-populated, refreshing CLAUDE_OAUTH credential from a prior successful run
  When the operator later re-runs "bin/agent-vault-approve-claude" with newer Claude token material to refresh the stored credential
  Then "bin/agent-vault-approve-claude" treats updating an already-populated CLAUDE_OAUTH credential as a supported path — it performs the owner login and re-POSTs the new access and refresh tokens to "POST /v1/credentials/oauth/tokens" rather than erroring because the credential already exists
  And after the update the CLAUDE_OAUTH credential carries the newly supplied token material and remains in a refreshing/connected state
